The most often used standard for
authorization currently is OAuth.

2
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:07,130
It is an open standard that was
specifically designed to be used on

3
00:00:07,130 --> 00:00:08,820
the Web with HTTP.

4
00:00:08,820 --> 00:00:11,970
As you can see, there are many
service providers that use OAuth.

5
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:15,790
Another popular standard that you may
have heard of is called OpenID connect.

6
00:00:15,790 --> 00:00:18,800
This is just a technology
built on top of OAuth 2.0.

7
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:22,050
Most big providers have adapted
to use OAuth version 2, and

8
